    "comment": "Rationale: IP3R1 was found in presynaptic ER of Purkinje cells by immunolabeling of rat cerebellar slices previously embedded in an agarose matrix.\n\n14/3/2017 Pim\n- Authors use an antibody to \"the IP3R\" receptor produced in (Mignery et al., 1989, PMID:2554146). There are multiple IP3R genes known today (in mouse 3: Itpr1-3). The antibody was generated to aa 482-500 (llghpphmnvnpqqpa-some aa's missing) of clone pcd 6035 (traced back to accession AAA88319.1). This sequence was blasted against the mouse refseq database. This region does show no detectable sequence similarity with the with the mouse and rat Itpr2 and Itpr3 genes.\n\nResults BLAST search to \"llghpphmnvnpqqpa\":\nmus Itpr1: 3-11\nmus Itpr2: NA\nmus Itpr3: NA\nrat Itpr2: 3-15 evalue\nrat Itpr2: 2.3 evalue\nrat Irpr3: NA\n\n- I approve annotation against rat Itpr1 using the featured antibody generated on mouse sequence.. Experimental description: Male Sprague-Dawley rats were used. However, other species were additionally used: bos taurus and chicken.",
